00:43.430 --> 00:47.299
<i>New York is a big city</i>
<i>with very small living spaces.</i>

00:47.333 --> 00:50.436
<i>A house party in Manhattan</i>
<i>makes intimate conversation</i>

00:50.470 --> 00:53.705
<i>not only possible,</i>
<i>but essential.</i>

00:53.740 --> 00:55.474
<i>And conversing intimately</i>

00:55.508 --> 00:58.076
<i>was one of the things</i>
<i>Weaver and I did best.</i>

00:58.111 --> 01:00.479
Yes, I-I wanna be
a journalist.

01:00.513 --> 01:03.115
Uh, but not the objective,
detached kind. Mm-hmm.

01:03.149 --> 01:04.449
I wanna use my own voice.

01:04.483 --> 01:06.585
You know, let people know
I've been there and seen it.

01:06.619 --> 01:08.353
Ah. You're a Gonzo.

01:08.388 --> 01:09.955
- Gonzo?
- Hunter Thompson.

01:09.989 --> 01:11.156
Gonzo journalism.

01:11.190 --> 01:13.191
Not to be confused
with Gonzo the Great...

01:13.226 --> 01:15.460
The greatest Muppet character
<i>ever.</i>

01:15.495 --> 01:17.095
Uh, yes. Blue fur,
purple feathers,

01:17.130 --> 01:18.430
wild-eyed optimism.
Mm-hmm.

01:18.464 --> 01:20.629
In love with, uh...

01:20.749 --> 01:22.183
Camilla the chicken.

01:22.217 --> 01:23.284
Yes.

01:23.318 --> 01:25.253
But anyway,
back to Hunter Thompson.

01:25.287 --> 01:26.654
- Right.
- You're out of cups.

01:26.688 --> 01:28.156
And this wine is cheaper
than my press-on nails.

01:28.190 --> 01:29.357
Oh, well.

01:29.391 --> 01:30.925
When in Rome.

01:30.959 --> 01:33.494
<i>♪ whoa, whoa,</i>
<i>whoa-oh-oh, whoa-whoa ♪</i>

01:33.529 --> 01:35.162
Why don't you two just
get a room already?

01:35.197 --> 01:37.164
This <i>is</i> Weaver's room.

01:37.199 --> 01:40.401
Oh, yeah. Then why don't you
kick everyone the hell out?

01:40.435 --> 01:41.669
Mmm.

01:41.703 --> 01:43.204
Bass player in a wifebeater.

01:43.238 --> 01:44.372
Yummy.

01:44.406 --> 01:45.773
Wow. She is a character.

01:45.807 --> 01:47.275
Oh, she sure is.

01:47.309 --> 01:49.677
You know, all these... all these
characters in our lives

01:49.711 --> 01:51.612
are fodder for our writing.
And then you see...

01:51.646 --> 01:53.981
You see that guy in the fedora
and the wader boots?

01:54.016 --> 01:55.149
Mm-hmm.

01:55.183 --> 01:56.384
That's, like, his uniform.

01:56.418 --> 01:59.520
He inspired my short play
"The Fishy Detective."

01:59.554 --> 02:01.388
Oh!

02:01.423 --> 02:02.490
- Right?
- I love it!

02:02.524 --> 02:05.259
- And I love dating a writer.
- Mmm.

02:05.293 --> 02:07.328
You wanna know
my favorite part?

02:07.362 --> 02:09.163
My devastating good looks
and killer charm?

02:10.365 --> 02:12.600
Listening to the clacking
of your typewriter

02:12.634 --> 02:14.201
when I'm falling asleep.

02:17.172 --> 02:18.305
♪ whoa, whoa,
whoa-oh-oh, whoa-whoa ♪

02:18.340 --> 02:20.874
